title: dahal-lashes-out-oli
summary: UCPN (Maoist) Chairman Pushpa Kamal Dhal has lashed out at CPN-UML Chairman KP Sharma Oli. “Oli is not the contractor or the king of this nation,” said leader Dahal, talking to media persons after meeting Constituent Assembly (CA) Chairman Subash Nembang at CA building in Nayabaneshwor, Kathmandu. On Saturday, the UCPN (Maoist) leaders walked out of the “decisive meeting” convened at the prime minister’s official residence in Baluwater right after UML leader Oli delivered his speech. The UCPN (Maoist) leaders were enraged after Oli said the new constitution should be drafted through procedure if the parties cannot forge agreement.

title: petrol-pumps-reopen-after-release-of-arrestees
summary: The petrol pumps in the Capital reopened after the release of two petroleum workers on Sunday. In the talks held with agitating Petroleum Workers Union, the Department of Commerce agreed to release the arrested workers. Earlier in the day, Petroleum Workers Union decided to shut down the fuel stations to protest the arreste of their fellow workers. The petroleum workers enforced shutdown of petrol pumps from Sunday demanding immediate release of their fellow workers.

title: four-electrocuted-as-high-tension-wire-snaps
summary: SINDHUPALCHOK, DEC 21 - Four people were  electrocuted  when a moving bus came in contact with a live wire here at Kattike in the district on Sunday. The deceased--two each women and men--were commuting by the bus. The bus heading for Jalbire from Kathmandu came in contact with a high tension wire after it snapped.
